cs.FL, cs.DM, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with automata and their computational power. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also likely as the paper involves studying the properties of monoids and graph products. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a possibility as the paper deals with the removal of lambda-transitions in automata. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper involves storage mechanisms in automata. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also less likely but possible as the paper deals with the computational power of automata with storage.
